properties.Name: Property
properties.Description:
A building or structure that a real estate mortgage loan is made upon.

It may or may not include the land around it or ground below it.

In the case of the oil and gas industry:

Land which is utilized for mining or oil and gas extraction purposes.

Mineral estate is distinct from real estate. Mineral owners have property rights over the mineral estate and they have a right to recover the mineral from the property owned.

Columns.Name: PropertyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Property.

Columns.Name: PropertyName
Columns.Description: The name of the property.

Columns.Name: PropertyDescription
Columns.Description:
A description of the property.

Ex:

"Spacious house is conveniently located in popular Briarcliff/Ridgefield Neighborhood - minutes to UNC/Duke, walking distance to pool and bus stop. Comfortable and flexible floor plan, guest suite with separate entrance, private backyard with hardwood trees, atrium breakfast area, screened porch, other fine features."

Columns.Name: PropertySize
Columns.Description: The size of the property.

Columns.Name: PropertySizeUomId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: PropertyDevelopedAcreage
Columns.Description: The number of acres that are allocated or assignable to productive wells or wells capable of production.

Columns.Name: PropertyUndevelopedAcreage
Columns.Description: Acreage on which wells have not been drilled or completed to a point that would permit the production of commercial quantities of oil and gas regardless of whether or not the acreage contains proved reserves.

Columns.Name: PropertyDevelopmentCompletedDate
Columns.Description: The date that development was completed on the property.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Description: The number of bedrooms in the property.

Columns.Description: The number of bathrooms in the property.

Columns.Name: Nabers
Columns.Description:
NABERS, the National Australian Built Environment Rating System, is an initiative by the government of Australia to measure and compare the environmental performance of Australian buildings and tenancies. There are NABERS rating tools for commercial office buildings to measure greenhouse gas emissions, energy efficiency, water efficiency, waste efficiency and indoor environment quality. There are also energy/greenhouse and water rating tools for hotels, shopping centers and data centers.

NABERS uses a 6 star to help Australian building owners understand their asset impact on the environment.

1 Star - Poor
2 Stars -  Below Average
3 Stars - Average
4 Stars - Good
5 Stars - Excellent
6 Stars - Market Leading

Partial stars are also awarded so that, for example, a NABERS Star Rating of 3.7 is possible and would indicate that the building is better than average but not quite at good.

Columns.Name: OfficeBuildingClass
Columns.Description:
Office Building Class provides a broad classification of office space. The core grades that are offered include:
A - Highest Quality - The most prestigious building with high quality standard features, state of the art systems 
B - Average - average systems and finishes
C - Poor - functional
Some grading systems may include +/-, AA, AAA, or Premium to help provide further differentiations between the grades

Columns.Name: LeedCertificationLevel
Columns.Description:
Leadership in Energy and Environmental DesignÂ® (LEED) is a rating system that is recognized as the international mark of excellence for green building in over 160 countries. LEED recognizes that sustainability should be at the heart of all buildings in their design, construction and operation.

Projects pursuing LEED certification earn points across several categories, including energy use and air quality. Based on the number of points achieved, a project then earns one of four LEED rating levels: Certified, Silver, Gold or Platinum.

Certified - 40-49 points earned
Silver - 50-59 points earned
Gold - 60-79 points earned
Platinum - 80+ points earned

Columns.Name: LastAppraisalDate
Columns.Description: The last appraisal of the property.

Columns.Name: LastAppraisalMarketValueAmount
Columns.Description: The market value as of the last appraisal date.

Columns.Name: LastAppraisalEquityAmount
Columns.Description: The difference between the market value of a property and the homeowner's outstanding mortgage balance.

Columns.Name: AskingPrice
Columns.Description: The asking price of the property.

Columns.Name: AdjustedBookBasisAmount
Columns.Description: The purchase price of a property plus any capital improvements less accrued depreciation, if any, to the date of the sale.

Columns.Name: EasementsStatement
Columns.Description: A right-of-way granted to a person or company authorizing access to or over the owner's land.

Columns.Name: EncroachmentsStatement
Columns.Description: An obstruction, building, or part of a building that intrudes beyond a legal boundary onto neighboring private or public land, or a building extending beyond the building line.

Columns.Name: JudgmentsDescription
Columns.Description:
A description of existing judgment(s) against the property.

Judgments are a decision made by a court of law. In judgments that require the repayment of a debt, the court may place a lien against the debtor's real property as collateral for the judgment's creditor.

A lien on the property of a debtor resulting from the decree of a court.

Columns.Name: MarketableTitleIndicator
Columns.Description: A title that is free and clear of objectionable liens, clouds, or other title defects. A title which enables an owner to sell his property freely to others and which others will accept without objection.

Columns.Name: NewHomeIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the property is a new home.

Columns.Name: OutstandingEncumbranceExistsIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that outstanding encumbrances exist upon the property.

Columns.Name: OwnerOccupiedPropertyIndicator
Columns.Description: "Owner Occupied" means the property is the owner's primary residence.

Columns.Name: NonOwnerOccupantIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the property is occupied by other than the owner.

Columns.Name: JudgmentExistsIndicator
Columns.Description:
A decision made by a court of law. In judgments that require the repayment of a debt, the court may place a lien against the debtor's real property as collateral for the judgment's creditor.

A lien on the property of a debtor resulting from the decree of a court.

Columns.Name: PrimaryResidenceIndicator
Columns.Description: The residential property physically occupied by an owner as the principal home domicile.

Columns.Name: NumberOfLeasedUnits
Columns.Description: The number of units that may be leased.

Columns.Name: AvailableLeaseSquareFootage
Columns.Description: The square footage of available leasable space.

Columns.Name: CurrentYearLeaseIncomeAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of lease income derived for the last year.

Columns.Name: NumberOfFloors
Columns.Description: The number of floor of the commercial property.

Columns.Name: FloorToAreaRatioFar
Columns.Description:
A ratio of the relationship between the total amount of floor space in a multi-story building and the base of that building. 

FARs are dictated by zoning laws, in effect, stipulate the maximum number of stories a building may have.

Columns.Name: TotalFloorSpaceSqFt
Columns.Description:
The total floor space of the building/property base, which is used to calculate the FAR.

FARs are dictated by zoning laws, in effect, stipulate the maximum number of stories a building may have.

Columns.Name: BuildingBaseSqFt
Columns.Description:
The square footage of the building/property base, which is used to calculate the FAR.

FARs are dictated by zoning laws, in effect, stipulate the maximum number of stories a building may have.

Columns.Name: CentralBusinessDistrictCbdPropertyIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the property is the downtown section of a city, generally consisting of retail, office, hotel, entertainment, and government land uses with some high-density housing.

Columns.Name: PropertyClearTitleIndicator
Columns.Description: A title that is free of liens or any legal question as to the ownership of the property.

Columns.Name: PropertyTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Property Type.

Columns.Name: OwnershipTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Ownership Type.

Columns.Name: TitleStatusId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Title Status.

Columns.Name: UsageTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Usage Type.

Properties.Description:
A building or structure that a real estate mortgage loan is made upon.

It may or may not include the land around it or ground below it.

In the case of the oil and gas industry:

Land which is utilized for mining or oil and gas extraction purposes.

Mineral estate is distinct from real estate. Mineral owners have property rights over the mineral estate and they have a right to recover the mineral from the property owned.
